      <span class="font-bold text-baits-blue">Temporary Bridging Loan</span> is a loan scheme supported by EnterpriseSG and granted to the borrower (a business entity) through the Participating Financial Institutions (PFIs). The loan, capped at S$5M, is repayable on equal monthly instalments over the approved loan tenor, capped at 5 years, depending on the approving financial institutions. The current risk sharing is 90% between EnterpriseSG and the PFIs.
      <br><br>
      <span class="font-bold text-baits-blue">Business Term Loan</span> is the financial institutionâ€™s in-house loan granted to the borrower (a business entity) and repayable on equal monthly instalments over the loan tenor which spans between 1 to 5 years, depending on the approving financial institution
      <br><br>
      <span class="font-bold text-baits-blue">Equipment/Machinery Loan</span> is a loan granted to the borrower (a business entity) for the purpose of financing the purchase of the Equipment/Machineries and repayable on equal monthly instalments over a maximum loan tenor which spans 5 years, depending on the approving financial institution.
      <br><br>
      <span class="font-bold text-baits-blue">Commercial Vehicle Loan</span> is a loan granted to the borrower (a business entity) for the purpose of financing the purchase of the commercial motor vehicles and repayable on equal monthly instalments over a maximum loan tenor which spans 5 years, depending on the approving financial institution.
      <br><br>
      <span class="font-bold text-baits-blue">Trade Financing</span> is a line of credit granted to the borrower (a business entity) backed by either Loan Insurance Scheme by EnterpriseSG or Fixed Deposits or Properties, for the purpose of financing the purchase of goods & services and repayable on bullet payment by the end of the tenor granted. Typical tenor spans between 60 - 180 days depending on the business nature of the borrower and approving financial institutions.
      <br><br>
      <span class="font-bold text-baits-blue">Factoring (Invoice Financing)</span> is a line of credit granted to the borrower (a business entity) backed by the invoices to customers (buyers), for the purpose of financing the receivables due to sale of goods & services and repayable on bullet payment by the end of the tenor granted. Typical tenor spans between 60 - 180 days depending on the business nature of the borrower and approving financial institutions.
      <br><br>
      <span class="font-bold text-baits-blue">Purchase Order Financing</span> is a line of credit and/or a loan granted to the borrower (a business entity) to finance the purchase orders received from the buyer(s) and repayable on bullet payment by the end of the approved tenor, typically between 30 to 90 days, depending on the approving financial institutions.
      <br><br>
      <span class="font-bold text-baits-blue">Supply Chain Financing</span> is a line of credit that has the characteristics of Factoring and Trade Financing worked into one. Approving financial institutions will oversee the whole purchase and sales of the deal by the borrower (a business entity), offsetting the payments required upon receipt of proceeds from the end-buyer.
      <br><br>
      <span class="font-bold text-baits-blue">Project Financing</span> is a combination of line of credit and loan granted to the borrower (a business entity) for the purpose of financing a particular project. The facility is usable only to the projects and will cease upon project completion. All purchases and proceeds will be co-managed by the approving financial institution.
      <br><br>
      <span class="font-bold text-baits-blue">Commercial Property Term Loan (New)</span> is a loan granted to the borrowers (a business entity) and repayable on equal monthly installments over the maximum loan tenor of 30 years depending on the leasehold of the property and approving financial institution.
      <br><br>
      <span class="font-bold text-baits-blue">Commercial Cash Out</span> is a loan granted to the borrowers (a business entity) on top of existing property term loan from the paid up and unencumbered value of the said property and is repayable on equal monthly installments over the maximum loan tenor of 10 years pegged depending on the leasehold of the property and approving financial institution.
      <br><br>
      <span class="font-bold text-baits-blue">Commercial Refinancing</span> is a loan granted to the borrowers (a business entity) when the financial institution is changed from current to another and repayable on equal monthly installments over the maximum loan tenor of 30 years depending on the leasehold of the property and the approving financial institution.
